istrict]] in [[United States House of Representatives elections in Indiana, 2002|2002]]<ref>https://www.ourcampaigns.com/RaceDetail.html?RaceID=232266</ref> and in [[United States House of Representatives elections in Indiana, 2010|2010]].<ref>https://www.ourcampaigns.com/RaceDetail.html?RaceID=621033</ref>\n\nOne of 20 Indiana State Senators who according to the Indianapolis Star Newspaper unfairly targeted the specialty license plates of the Indiana Youth Group, resulting in not only the Indiana Youth Group having their specialty plates revoked but also those of 4-H and The Greenway Foundation.  Senator Young was one of 20 Indiana State Senators who signed a letter to the BMV to have the specialty plates for IYG revoked as a direct attack because IYG provides a safe place for LGBT teenagers.\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n* [https://ballotpedia.org/R._Michael_Young_(Indiana) R. Michael Young at Ballotpedia]\n*[https://www.ourcampaigns.com/CandidateDetail.html?CandidateID=40418 Our Campaigns \u2013 Senator R. Michael Young (IN)] profile\n* [http://www.in.gov/legislative/senate_republicans/homepages/s35/ State Senator R. Michael Young] ''official Indiana State Legislature site''\n* {{CongLinks | congbio= | votesmart=4728 | fec= | congress= }}<!--\nLinks formerly displayed via the CongLinks template:\n* [http://www.followthemoney.org/database/uniquecandidate.phtml?uc=139183 Financial information (state office)] at the National Institute for Money in State Politics\n* -->\n\n{{Indiana State Senators}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Young, R. Michael}}\n[[Category:Indiana state senators]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Indianapolis]]\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American politicians]]\n\n\n{{Indiana-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 1980-1982 \u2192 1980\u20131982", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/R._Michae